Introduction

KISS, also known as Korea International Super Star, was a three-member girl group under J-Entercom. They made their debut on December 18, 2001, with their first studio album "Kiss First Album". The group disbanded in March 2002 due to internal conflicts.

In 2016, during episode 36 of "Two Yoo Project – Sugar Man", the members reunited and revealed that they actually disbanded because one member was dating someone, which was against the label's rules.
